<p><i><b>Halo 3</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/First-person_shooter" title="First-person shooter">first-person shooter</a> <a href="/wiki/Video_game" title="Video game">video game</a> developed by <a href="/wiki/Bungie" title="Bungie">Bungie</a> exclusively for the <a href="/wiki/Xbox_360" title="Xbox 360">Xbox 360</a>. The game is the third title in the <a href="/wiki/Halo_(series)" title="Halo (series)"><i>Halo</i> series</a> and concludes the <a href="/wiki/Story_arc" title="Story arc">story arc</a> that began in <i><a href="/wiki/Halo:_Combat_Evolved" title="Halo: Combat Evolved">Halo: Combat Evolved</a></i> and continued in <i><a href="/wiki/Halo_2" title="Halo 2">Halo 2</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-announcement_6-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-announcement-6" title=""><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup> The game was released on September 25, 2007 in Australia, Brazil, India, New Zealand, North America, and Singapore;<sup id="cite_ref-releasedate_3-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-releasedate-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> September 26, 2007 in Europe; and September 27, 2007 in Japan. On the day before its official release, 4.2 million units of <i>Halo 3</i> were in retail outlets.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7" title=""><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>Halo 3</i><span style="padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>s story centers on the interstellar war between 26th century humanity, led by the <a href="/wiki/United_Nations_Space_Command" title="United Nations Space Command" class="mw-redirect">United Nations Space Command</a>, and a collection of alien races known as the <a href="/wiki/Covenant_(Halo)" title="Covenant (Halo)">Covenant</a>. The player assumes the role of the <a href="/wiki/Master_Chief_(Halo)" title="Master Chief (Halo)">Master Chief</a>, a cybernetically enhanced supersoldier, as he wages war in defense of humanity, assisted by human <a href="/wiki/Marine_(military)" title="Marine (military)">Marines</a> as well as an allied alien race called <a href="/wiki/Elite_(Halo)" title="Elite (Halo)">Elites</a>, which is led by the <a href="/wiki/Arbiter_(Halo)" title="Arbiter (Halo)">Arbiter</a>. The game features vehicles, weapons, and gameplay not present in previous titles of the series, as well as the addition of saved gameplay films, file sharing, and the Forge map editor; a utility which allows the player to perform modifications to multiplayer levels.</p>
<p><i>Halo 3</i> grossed US$300 million in its first week.<sup id="cite_ref-sales_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sales-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> More than one million people played <i>Halo 3</i> on <a href="/wiki/Xbox_Live" title="Xbox Live">Xbox Live</a> in the first twenty hours.<sup id="cite_ref-1milxbox_9-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1milxbox-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup> As of January 3, 2008, <i>Halo 3</i> has sold 8.1 million copies,<sup id="cite_ref-2008-01-03_sales_10-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2008-01-03_sales-10" title=""><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup> and was the <a href="/wiki/2007_in_video_gaming#United_States" title="2007 in video gaming">best-selling video game of 2007 in the U.S.</a><sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11" title=""><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup> Overall, the game was very well-received by critics, with the Forge and <a href="/wiki/Multiplayer" title="Multiplayer" class="mw-redirect">multiplayer</a> offerings singled out as strong features. By March 2009 more than 1 billion online matches had been played online.<sup id="cite_ref-gi-1bil_12-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gi-1bil-12" title=""><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> A prequel to the game, <i><a href="/wiki/Halo_3:_ODST" title="Halo 3: ODST">Halo 3: ODST</a></i>, is currently under development.</p>
