</table>
<p><i>Halo 3</i> was released in three separate versions. The Standard Edition contains the game disc, manual, and a small poster with the game's control-map and artwork.</p>
<p>The Limited Edition, contained in a metal case, contains the game disc, manual, poster, interactive Xbox 360 bonus disc with several featurettes, and a hard cover bound "Bestiarum", which is a collection of information and art covering the species, cultures, and civilizations of <i>Halo 3</i>.</p>
<p>The final version was marketed as the "Legendary Edition", which contains the game disc, manual, poster, interactive bonus disc, Bestiarum (on one of the DVD discs), Legendary DVD containing special content exclusive to the Legendary Edition, and a scale replica of the Master Chief's helmet as a case for the three discs. The slip-cover packaging unfolds into a large heavy-stock poster of Master Chief.<sup id="cite_ref-versions_73-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-versions-73" title=""><span>[</span>74<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Gamestation" title="Gamestation">Gamestation</a> stores in the UK also offered a limited edition Master Chief figurine only available to the first 1000 pre-orders.<sup id="cite_ref-74" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-74" title=""><span>[</span>75<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Upon release, some of the Limited Edition versions of <i>Halo 3</i> were found to have a defect in the hub that kept the discs in place, which could lead to scratched discs. Microsoft confirmed the problem and offered to replace scratched <i>Halo 3</i> Limited Edition discs free of charge until the end of January 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-75" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-75" title=""><span>[</span>76<span>]</span></a></sup> This was not a problem in either the Legendary Edition or the Standard Edition.<sup id="cite_ref-76" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-76" title=""><span>[</span>77<span>]</span></a></sup><br clear="all" /></p>
<p><a name="Sales" id="Sales"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Sales</span></h3>
<p>According to Microsoft, first-day sales of <i>Halo 3</i> reached $170 million in the U.S., setting a record for highest gross of an entertainment product within 24 hours of its release.<sup id="cite_ref-170M_77-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-170M-77" title=""><span>[</span>78<span>]</span></a></sup> The performance beat the previous record setter—<i>Halo 2</i>—which earned $125 million within 24 hours after its launch.<sup id="cite_ref-170M_77-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-170M-77" title=""><span>[</span>78<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Halo 3</i> broke other records as well; at least four million copies of <i>Halo 3</i> were pre-ordered globally, making it the fastest pre-selling game to date.<sup id="cite_ref-78" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-78" title=""><span>[</span>79<span>]</span></a></sup> Worldwide more than US$300 million worth were sold in the first week, helping to more than double the sales of the Xbox 360 when compared with the weekly average before the <i>Halo 3</i> launch.<sup id="cite_ref-sales_8-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sales-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<div class="thumb tleft">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_Halo_3_launch.jpg" class="image" title="Bill Gates sold copies of the game at the launch in Bellevue, WA."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Bill_Gates_Halo_3_launch.jpg/180px-Bill_Gates_Halo_3_launch.jpg" width="180" height="120" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_Halo_3_launch.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="/wiki/Bill_Gates" title="Bill Gates">Bill Gates</a> sold copies of the game at the launch in Bellevue, WA.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In the U.S., <i>Halo 3</i> sold 3.3 million copies in its first 12 days on sale,<sup id="cite_ref-79" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-79" title=""><span>[</span>80<span>]</span></a></sup> increasing to 3.7 million copies by November 15, 2007.<sup id="cite_ref-80" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-80" title=""><span>[</span>81<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Reuters" title="Reuters">Reuters</a> UK estimated that <i>Halo 3</i> may have sold up to 5.2 million copies worldwide in the first two weeks after launch.<sup id="cite_ref-sales_8-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sales-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> By November 30, 2007, <i>Halo 3</i> had sold 5 million copies worldwide, and as of that point, was the <a href="/wiki/2007_in_video_gaming#United_States" title="2007 in video gaming">best-selling video game of 2007 in the U.S.</a>, even though the game is only available on one console.<sup id="cite_ref-81" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-81" title=""><span>[</span>82<span>]</span></a></sup> On January 3, 2008, Microsoft announced that <i>Halo 3</i> has sold 8.1 million copies.<sup id="cite_ref-2008-01-03_sales_10-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2008-01-03_sales-10" title=""><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup> The game drew over a million <a href="/wiki/Xbox_Live" title="Xbox Live">Xbox Live</a> members to play online in the first 20 hours, making it the biggest day for Xbox Live gaming in history.<sup id="cite_ref-1milxbox_9-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1milxbox-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup> The game returned to the top 20 sales charts more than a year after its release in February 2009; Gamasutra reported that the boost might have been due to the release of <i><a href="/wiki/Halo_Wars" title="Halo Wars">Halo Wars</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-82" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-82" title=""><span>[</span>83<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>Advertising Age</i> reported that movie studio executives were convinced the release of <i>Halo 3</i> harmed box office receipts; the week's take was 27% less than the previous year's yield.<sup id="cite_ref-83" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-83" title=""><span>[</span>84<span>]</span></a></sup> While some executives decided the disparity in estimated and actual gross for films like <i><a href="/wiki/The_Heartbreak_Kid_(2007_film)" title="The Heartbreak Kid (2007 film)">The Heartbreak Kid</a></i> was due more to the film's poor reception, other analysts believed that "the audience on [<i>Halo 3</i>] is the 18-to-34 demographic, similar to what you'd see in cinemas" and that this led to a decrease in receipts.<sup id="cite_ref-84" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-84" title=""><span>[</span>85<span>]</span></a></sup> Later research suggested that the <i>Halo 3</i> players still watched the same amount of television and movies, regardless of the time they spent playing the game.<sup id="cite_ref-85" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-85" title=""><span>[</span>86<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Downloadable_content" id="Downloadable_content"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">Downloadable content</span></h2>
<p><i>Halo 3</i> supports multiplayer map downloadable content as well as game updates via <a href="/wiki/Xbox_Live" title="Xbox Live">Xbox Live</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-86" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-86" title=""><span>[</span>87<span>]</span></a></sup> The first three post-release multiplayer maps, "Standoff", "Rat's Nest", and "Foundry", were released as a pack on December 11, 2007, collectively known as the "Heroic Map Pack".<sup id="cite_ref-bungieheroic_87-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bungieheroic-87" title=""><span>[</span>88<span>]</span></a></sup> "Foundry" in particular expanded the map-creation abilities available through Forge with a greater range of relatively primitive objects, and a clear open design.</p>
<p>The second three maps were released in the "Legendary Map Pack", on April 15, 2008. These were three new maps entitled "Ghost Town", "Avalanche", and "Blackout"; the latter two maps are remakes of the <i>Halo: Combat Evolved</i> map "Sidewinder" and the <i>Halo 2</i> map "Lockout" respectively.<sup id="cite_ref-legendarypack_88-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-legendarypack-88" title=""><span>[</span>89<span>]</span></a></sup> These maps introduced visual filters to the Forge pallet, which change the way the maps look.<sup id="cite_ref-89" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-89" title=""><span>[</span>90<span>]</span></a></sup> A remake of the <i>Halo: Combat Evolved</i> map "Chill Out", titled "Cold Storage", was released as a free download on "Bungie Day", July 7, 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-90" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-90" title=""><span>[</span>91<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The third multiplayer map pack, titled the "Mythic Map Pack" and consisting of the maps "Orbital", "Assembly", and "Sandbox", was included with the Limited Collectors Edition of <i><a href="/wiki/Halo_Wars" title="Halo Wars">Halo Wars</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-91" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-91" title=""><span>[</span>92<span>]</span></a></sup> The map pack is scheduled for release over the Xbox Live Marketplace on April 9, 2009. Like "Foundry", "Sandbox" also expands upon Forge map-creation with several cleared areas.<sup id="cite_ref-92" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-92" title=""><span>[</span>93<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The first version update for <i>Halo 3</i> was released on February 19, 2008, and addressed various bugs such as melee contest resolution and saved-film theater errors.<sup id="cite_ref-93" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-93" title=""><span>[</span>94<span>]</span></a></sup> The next update (called a Title Update) was released September 23, 2008, and includes new Achievements, a new <a href="/wiki/Experience_point" title="Experience point">XP</a> ranking system, and various new ways to detect and stop cheating in the game.<sup id="cite_ref-94" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-94" title=""><span>[</span>95<span>]</span></a></sup> There are no further updates planned for <i>Halo 3</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-95" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-95" title=""><span>[</span>96<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
