<p><i>Halo 3</i> was given favorable reviews from game critics. On the review aggregator <a href="/wiki/Game_Rankings" title="Game Rankings" class="mw-redirect">Game Rankings</a>, the game has an average score of 93%, based on 90 reviews, making it the seventh best reviewed Xbox 360 game to date.<sup id="cite_ref-gr_97-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gr-97" title=""><span>[</span>98<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-98" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-98" title=""><span>[</span>99<span>]</span></a></sup> On <a href="/wiki/Metacritic" title="Metacritic">Metacritic</a>, the game has an average score of 94 out of 100, based on 74 reviews.<sup id="cite_ref-99" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-99" title=""><span>[</span>100<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i><a href="/wiki/Pro-G" title="Pro-G" class="mw-redirect">Pro-G</a></i> assured readers in its review that <i>Halo 3</i> lived up to the hype, saying that the game "is everything we hoped it would be, and much, much, more".<sup id="cite_ref-progrev_100-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-progrev-100" title=""><span>[</span>101<span>]</span></a></sup> Many publications, including <i><a href="/wiki/Eurogamer" title="Eurogamer">Eurogamer</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Games_Radar" title="Games Radar" class="mw-redirect">Games Radar</a></i> stated that the "winning formula" of <i>Halo</i> and <i>Halo 2</i> was unchanged, but the addition of new features and weapons prevented stagnation.<sup id="cite_ref-101" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-101" title=""><span>[</span>102<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-102" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-102" title=""><span>[</span>103<span>]</span></a></sup> Most publications agreed that multiplayer was by far one of the best features; IGN said that the multiplayer map lineup was the strongest of the series,<sup id="cite_ref-ignrev_103-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ignrev-103" title=""><span>[</span>104<span>]</span></a></sup> and Gamespy added that the multiplayer offering will make "<i>Halo</i> [veterans] weep big sloppy sobs of joy".<sup id="cite_ref-gamespy_review_104-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gamespy_review-104" title=""><span>[</span>105<span>]</span></a></sup> The Forge level editor and saved films features were singled out as particularly strong features,<sup id="cite_ref-Gamespot_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gamespot-18" title=""><span>[</span>19<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-105" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-105" title=""><span>[</span>106<span>]</span></a></sup> in addition to superb voice acting and Martin O'Donnell's rich score.<sup id="cite_ref-gamespy_review_104-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gamespy_review-104" title=""><span>[</span>105<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-game_informer_review_106-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-game_informer_review-106" title=""><span>[</span>107<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Reception of the single-player aspect varied greatly. <i>Pro-G</i> said that while the <a href="/wiki/Cliffhanger" title="Cliffhanger">cliffhanger</a> ending of <i>Halo 2</i> was disappointing, the campaign of <i>Halo 3</i> "is anything but";<sup id="cite_ref-progrev_100-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-progrev-100" title=""><span>[</span>101<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/GameSpot" title="GameSpot">GameSpot</a> and <a href="/wiki/GameSpy" title="GameSpy">GameSpy</a>, meanwhile, said that the campaign was too short, especially on easier difficulty levels.<sup id="cite_ref-Gamespot_18-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gamespot-18" title=""><span>[</span>19<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-gamespy_review_104-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gamespy_review-104" title=""><span>[</span>105<span>]</span></a></sup> IGN was highly critical of the eighth level, stating "the penultimate chapter is so bad, just thinking about it puts a rotten taste in my mouth." <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title="The New York Times">The New York Times</a></i> said the game had a "throwaway" plot and Total Video Games judged the single-player aspect ultimately disappointing.<sup id="cite_ref-nytreview_107-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nytreview-107" title=""><span>[</span>108<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-tvg_review_108-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-tvg_review-108" title=""><span>[</span>109<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Other complaints focused on the <a href="/wiki/Game_artificial_intelligence" title="Game artificial intelligence">artificial intelligence</a>; critics praised the enemy AI but complained that the intelligence of the player's allies was far poorer.<sup id="cite_ref-ign_review_16-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ign_review-16" title=""><span>[</span>17<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Gamespot_18-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gamespot-18" title=""><span>[</span>19<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-gamecritics_review_109-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gamecritics_review-109" title=""><span>[</span>110<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-110" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-110" title=""><span>[</span>111<span>]</span></a></sup> Bryan Vore of <i><a href="/wiki/Game_Informer" title="Game Informer">Game Informer</a></i> said that human faces and some textures were just "embarrassing".<sup id="cite_ref-game_informer_review_106-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-game_informer_review-106" title=""><span>[</span>107<span>]</span></a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Game_Informer" title="Game Informer">Game Informer</a></i> criticized the occasional repeated environments and poor final boss battle, and both IGN and CinemaBlend.com said that they thought a part of the story was lost by not having the <a href="/wiki/Arbiter_(Halo)" title="Arbiter (Halo)">Arbiter</a> featuring as prominently as the character was in <i>Halo 2</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-ign_review_16-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ign_review-16" title=""><span>[</span>17<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-111" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-111" title=""><span>[</span>112<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>Halo 3</i> was nominated for seven awards from the <a href="/wiki/Spike_TV" title="Spike TV" class="mw-redirect">Spike TV Awards</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-112" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-112" title=""><span>[</span>113<span>]</span></a></sup> of which it won "Best Multiplayer Game" and "Most Addictive Video Game Fueled by Dew".<sup id="cite_ref-113" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-113" title=""><span>[</span>114<span>]</span></a></sup> It won <a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)"><i>TIME</i> magazine's</a> "Game of the Year" and <a href="/wiki/IGN" title="IGN">IGN</a> chose it as the Best Xbox 360 Online Multiplayer Game and Innovative Design of 2007.<sup id="cite_ref-114" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-114" title=""><span>[</span>115<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-115" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-115" title=""><span>[</span>116<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-116" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-116" title=""><span>[</span>117<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Halo 3</i> won "Multiplayer Game of the Year" and "Geezer Game of the Year" as awarded by Geezer Gamers as well as runner-up for "Best Shooter".<sup id="cite_ref-117" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-117" title=""><span>[</span>118<span>]</span></a></sup> The <a href="/wiki/Visual_Effects_Society" title="Visual Effects Society">Visual Effects Society</a> awarded Bungie the "Best Real Time Visuals in a Video Game" for <i>Halo 3</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-118" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-118" title=""><span>[</span>119<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Halo 3</i> took the <i>Calvin Award</i> for "Best Videogame" as selected by <a href="/wiki/Box_Office_Prophets" title="Box Office Prophets">Box Office Prophets</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-119" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-119" title=""><span>[</span>120<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Halo 3</i> also took the award for Xbox 360 Game of the Year 2007 from <a href="/wiki/Gametrailers.com" title="Gametrailers.com" class="mw-redirect">Gametrailers.com</a>, and was voted by fans as Game of the Year on <a href="/wiki/G-Phoria" title="G-Phoria">G-Phoria</a>. <i>Halo 3</i> won the <i><a href="/wiki/Edge_(magazine)" title="Edge (magazine)">Edge</a></i> Award For Interactive Innovation in August 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-120" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-120" title=""><span>[</span>121<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Halo_3:_ODST" id="Halo_3:_ODST"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline"><i>Halo 3: ODST</i></span></h2>
<div class="rellink noprint relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Halo_3:_ODST" title="Halo 3: ODST">Halo 3: ODST</a></div>
<p>Bungie announced on October 9, 2008, that a standalone expansion of <i>Halo 3</i> entitled <i>Halo 3: Recon</i>. This was later changed to <i>Halo 3: ODST</i>. It is scheduled for release in the third quarter of 2009.<sup id="cite_ref-Halo_3:_Recon_121-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Halo_3:_Recon-121" title=""><span>[</span>122<span>]</span></a></sup> In the game, the players assume the role of a UNSC Orbital Drop Shock Trooper (ODST), instead of the Master Chief. The events of the game are a prequel to <i>Halo 3</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-Halo_3:_Recon_121-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Halo_3:_Recon-121" title=""><span>[</span>122<span>]</span></a></sup><br clear="all" /></p>
<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
